title: NY, Missouri governors make World Series bet
text: The Mets have more than just a World Series on the line. If they lose, Gov. Andrew Cuomo will have to wear a Kansas City Royals jersey to work. Cuomo and Missouri Gov. Jay Nixon today announced a friendly wager on the World Series matchup between the Mets the Royals. The series starts Tuesday night.
